19:25.680 --> 19:27.680
Number three.

19:37.120 --> 19:38.720
Number four.

19:50.000 --> 19:51.440
Number five.

19:54.720 --> 19:56.720
Number six.

20:08.720 --> 20:09.680
Number six.

20:25.360 --> 20:27.360
Number seven.

20:37.360 --> 20:39.360
Number eight.

20:39.360 --> 20:51.040
Number nine.

21:10.160 --> 21:12.160
Number ten.

21:27.360 --> 21:29.360
Curing a cold.

21:31.360 --> 21:33.360
The first sneeze.

21:34.160 --> 21:39.600
When the White House of Virginia City, Nevada burnt down,

21:40.720 --> 21:48.000
I lost my home, my happiness, my health, and my trunk.

21:49.680 --> 21:53.600
The loss of my home and my happiness was not a problem.

21:54.880 --> 22:00.960
A home without a mother or a sister who care for you isn't really a home.

22:01.760 --> 22:05.520
The loss of my happiness was not a problem either.

22:06.960 --> 22:11.680
I'm not a poet and so I'm usually a happy person.

22:13.680 --> 22:20.480
But the loss of my good health and of my handsome trunk was a serious problem.

22:22.400 --> 22:26.320
On the day of the fire, I caught a terrible cold.

22:26.800 --> 22:41.600
The first time I began to sneeze, a friend told me to put my feet in hot water and then go to bed.

22:42.720 --> 22:43.360
I did this.

22:45.120 --> 22:50.400
The next day, another friend advised me to take a cold shower.

22:51.520 --> 22:52.640
I did this too.

22:56.320 --> 23:11.200
After an hour, another friend told me to eat a big quantity of good food.

23:11.840 --> 23:17.600
So I went to a new restaurant and started to eat everything I saw.

23:19.520 --> 23:25.200
The owner of the restaurant asked me if the people of Virginia City often had colds.

23:26.480 --> 23:27.840
I answered that they did.

23:29.040 --> 23:34.720
He then went outside, took down the new sign and closed the restaurant.

23:36.800 --> 23:39.520
That day, I met another good friend.

23:40.560 --> 23:44.240
He told me that I must drink a bottle of warm salt water.

23:45.920 --> 23:48.640
This was the only remedy to cure a cold.

23:50.320 --> 23:53.600
I tried it and the result was surprising.

23:54.400 --> 23:57.600
I threw up everything I had in my stomach.

23:58.720 --> 24:02.080
I will never drink warm salt water again.

24:03.120 --> 24:06.080
And I will never advise anyone to do so.

24:07.280 --> 24:13.280
I prefer being in a California earthquake than drinking a bottle of warm salt water.

24:14.400 --> 24:21.520
This horrible remedy did not cure my cold and it made my stomach sick for some time.

24:23.760 --> 24:30.400
I continued to sneeze violently at shoe and shoe to blow my nose

24:33.920 --> 24:36.240
and to destroy handkerchiefs.

24:38.560 --> 24:40.720
My suffering grew.

24:40.720 --> 24:46.480
The remedies.

24:48.560 --> 24:53.840
One day, I met a woman who appeared to be 150 years old.

24:55.200 --> 25:00.160
She came from a deserted part of the far west where there were no doctors.

25:01.600 --> 25:05.360
She had years of experience helping sick people.

25:06.240 --> 25:13.760
She prepared a special mixture of molasses, aquafortis, oils and other strange drugs.

25:14.640 --> 25:19.040
She advised me to drink a glass of this mixture every 15 minutes.

25:21.120 --> 25:23.760
I only drank one glass of the mixture.

25:24.720 --> 25:26.640
It was enough to make me crazy.

25:27.440 --> 25:30.880
I became extremely mean and dangerous.

25:32.240 --> 25:34.160
My mind was full of wild thoughts.

25:35.120 --> 25:37.040
My behavior was horrible.

25:38.080 --> 25:40.720
I was proud of being bad.

25:42.960 --> 25:47.840
After a few days, the effect of the horrible mixture passed.

25:49.200 --> 25:50.720
I felt a lot worse.

25:52.160 --> 25:54.960
My cold passed from my head to my lungs.

25:55.760 --> 26:01.600
I coughed every moment of the day and of the night.

26:01.600 --> 26:05.120
It was impossible to sleep.

26:06.640 --> 26:09.360
The sound of my voice frightened me.

26:11.600 --> 26:13.280
I got worse every day.

26:14.560 --> 26:17.600
An old friend recommended gin.

26:18.720 --> 26:19.440
I drank it.

26:20.960 --> 26:24.160
Then I drank gin with molasses.

26:25.440 --> 26:27.760
Finally, I added onions.

26:28.720 --> 26:32.800
So I had gin, molasses and onions.

26:34.160 --> 26:37.440
The smell of my breath was terrible.

26:41.520 --> 26:43.360
The San Francisco remedy.

26:45.280 --> 26:48.800
I decided to travel to the countryside to improve my health.

26:50.640 --> 26:54.000
I went to Lake Bigler with my friend Wilson.

26:54.880 --> 26:58.320
We traveled in a comfortable pioneer coach.

26:59.920 --> 27:04.400
At Lake Bigler, we fished and sailed on the lake.

27:06.080 --> 27:08.080
We hunted for hours in the woods.

27:09.040 --> 27:11.360
In the evening, we danced.

27:11.920 --> 27:14.240
I enjoyed myself greatly.

27:15.520 --> 27:18.480
But my illness got worse.

27:20.240 --> 27:22.400
A tourist at Lake Bigler

27:23.200 --> 27:25.600
recommended a cold sheet bath.

27:26.800 --> 27:28.400
I never refused a remedy.

27:30.160 --> 27:35.280
At midnight, when it was very cold, I undressed completely.

27:36.560 --> 27:39.680
I covered my body with a wet ice cold sheet.

27:40.960 --> 27:44.560
I kept the sheet on my body for a long time.

27:45.920 --> 27:48.880
It was the worst experience of my life.

27:49.840 --> 27:55.200
The wet ice cold sheet made my blood freeze and made my heart stop.

27:56.480 --> 27:59.360
I thought it was time for me to die.

28:03.760 --> 28:05.920
Never take a sheet bath.

28:07.360 --> 28:07.760
Never.

28:08.880 --> 28:10.800
This is my advice to everyone.

28:12.560 --> 28:14.400
My condition got a lot worse.

28:15.120 --> 28:17.360
Other people recommended other remedies.

28:18.000 --> 28:20.880
Not one of these remedies cured my cold.

28:22.880 --> 28:28.480
After a week at Lake Bigler, I decided to go to Steamboat Springs.

28:29.440 --> 28:33.200
I thought that the hot baths there were good for my health.

28:34.480 --> 28:35.440
They were not.

28:36.880 --> 28:41.520
While I was at Steamboat Springs, I tried several different remedies.

28:42.240 --> 28:45.120
But I just got worse and worse.

28:46.080 --> 28:47.120
I was desperate.

28:49.520 --> 28:53.120
I finally decided to visit the city of San Francisco.

28:54.240 --> 29:01.440
The day I arrived, a woman at the hotel told me to drink a bottle of whiskey every 24 hours.

29:03.200 --> 29:08.880
A dear friend who lived in San Francisco recommended exactly the same thing.

29:08.880 --> 29:11.920
A bottle of whiskey every 24 hours.

29:12.560 --> 29:14.560
That's two bottles of whiskey.

29:15.280 --> 29:22.720
Well, I am happy to say that this San Francisco remedy finally cured my cold.

29:27.200 --> 29:28.800
A city is born.

29:30.800 --> 29:41.440
A Spanish explorer, Gaspard de Portola, discovered San Francisco Bay in 1769.

29:42.400 --> 29:45.520
And he built a Presidio there.

29:46.720 --> 29:58.400
At the beginning of the 1800s, San Francisco, then called Yerba Buena, was a sleepy Spanish village.

29:59.760 --> 30:08.800
There was a Presidio, a Spanish church called Mission Dolores, and some simple homes.

30:09.600 --> 30:12.480
There were a few ships in the Big Harbor.

30:14.480 --> 30:19.920
With the discovery of gold in 1848, everything changed.

30:20.800 --> 30:24.400
San Francisco suddenly became a busy city.

30:25.600 --> 30:31.840
In only one year, its population went from 1,000 to 30,000.

30:33.440 --> 30:36.400
Settlers came from all parts of the world.

30:37.040 --> 30:41.680
There was a population explosion in California.

30:42.880 --> 30:49.520
The new settlers needed all types of things from the industries on the east coast.

30:50.720 --> 30:57.200
The Sea Route from New York to San Francisco became an important one.

30:58.560 --> 31:05.600
The city of San Francisco became the most important settlement on the Pacific coast.

31:07.200 --> 31:11.680
The city and its port were full of life.

31:13.520 --> 31:18.000
The gold miners often went to San Francisco to sell their gold,

31:18.800 --> 31:21.760
to buy supplies, and to have fun.

31:23.200 --> 31:25.920
Those were exciting times.

31:30.560 --> 31:32.320
San Francisco today.

31:33.280 --> 31:38.160
Today, San Francisco is a beautiful metropolis by the bay.

31:39.200 --> 31:43.520
It is an international, commercial, and banking center.

31:44.720 --> 31:49.920
People from all parts of the world live and work there in harmony.

31:50.960 --> 31:56.160
San Francisco has always been a friendly city.

31:56.560 --> 32:04.160
Each year, thousands of tourists visit its unforgettable attractions.

32:05.920 --> 32:11.360
There is a big, colorful Chinese neighborhood called Chinatown.

32:12.960 --> 32:20.320
North Beach is the old Italian settlement with typical Italian food shops and cafes.

32:20.320 --> 32:28.320
Music, art, and theater are an important part of life in San Francisco.

32:29.440 --> 32:33.520
There are several excellent museums and universities.

32:35.440 --> 32:38.320
The city is built on steep hills.

32:39.600 --> 32:43.920
This fact gives it unusual beauty and extraordinary views.

32:44.240 --> 32:51.360
The architecture is a mix of modern skyscrapers and Victorian buildings.

32:53.120 --> 33:00.080
The gold rush days are over now, but San Francisco is still an exciting place.

33:00.080 --> 33:14.560
From this valley, they say you are going.

33:15.360 --> 33:18.320
I will miss your bright eyes and sweet smile.

33:19.200 --> 33:25.920
For I know you are taking the sunshine that has lighted my pathway a while.

33:26.880 --> 33:29.920
Come and sit by my side if you love me.

33:30.640 --> 33:33.360
Do not hasten to bid me adieu.

33:34.320 --> 33:40.960
But remember the Red River Valley and the one that has loved you so true.

